klZy52wh0LKWpFKaOUUR0Jvp1gFPQ ) and especially after. It=E2=80=99s worth co=
nsidering, though, why their approach might not work out. I see two risk fa=
ctors:

* First, it=E2=80=99s possible that large models simply become so capable t=
hat it is ultimately untenable to stick to Apple=E2=80=99s more limited app=
roach. This is the world where Gemini becomes so good that Android is meani=
ngfully differentiated from the iPhone, or where OpenAI can actually build =
a competitive device of their own. Apple is hedging against this possibilit=
y with its partnership with OpenAI, and willingness to partner with other l=
arge language models (although I have heard the company gave the cold shoul=
der to Meta), but this remains the biggest bear case for Apple.
* Second, Apple has to actually execute in an area where they haven=E2=80=
=99t proven they have the expertise to do so. The blog post I discussed abo=
ve has various evaluation scores that rank Apple=E2=80=99s models quite hig=
hly for their class, but the proof of their capability will be in real worl=
d use cases. I was mildly surprised that Apple stuck with the =E2=80=9CSiri=
=E2=80=9D branding, given the extent to which large swathes of people, incl=
uding yours truly, have been disappointed in the extent to which the produc=
t has fallen short of the promise; Apple needs to avoid doubling down on th=
ose failures.

I do remain optimistic on all counts. I=E2=80=99m unconvinced that large la=
nguage models are going to be sufficiently powerful enough to displace iOS,=
 and that Apple=E2=80=99s approach to productize LLM capability around data=
 that only they have access to, while Aggregating more powerful models, is =
going to be successful, but time will tell. Relatedly, the speed with which=
 a wide array of model builders delivered useful models both gives me confi=
dence that Apple=E2=80=99s models will be good enough, and that there isn=
=E2=80=99t some sort of special sauce that will lead to one model breaking =
away from the pack. At the same time, truly integrating personal data via R=
AG isn=E2=80=99t going to easy: there is an aspect where Apple is going to =
need to truly innovate in a field where they haven=E2=80=99t shown much lea=
dership.

Ultimately, though, I believe that structural positions in value chains mat=
ter, which is why I wrote Apple Intelligence is Right on Time ( https://str=
