The Talk Show Live
------------------

I did watch the The Talk Show Live via the Apple Vision Pro ( https://darin=
gfireball.net/linked/2024/06/10/sandwich-theater ) ; it was definitely a fi=
rst-time-ever sort of experience, as I had to force-quit the app and restar=
t the stream on several occasions, but it was overall a cool experience. On=
e interesting takeaway is that the broadcast was constrained to a box in yo=
ur field of view, as opposed to encompassing your entire field of view. I d=
o think this distinction is significant: while the 3D nature of the broadca=
st was interesting, it ultimately felt closer to a watching something on TV=
 as opposed to feeling like you were actually there.

Setting aside the technology, there were two interesting takeaways from the=
 interviews themselves.

First, Senior Vice President of Machine Learning and AI Strategy John Giann=
andrea was both an excellent interviewee, and also explained why Apple is t=
aking a pretty hands-off approach to moderation for AI. This is both encour=
aging and also strikes me as a bit of a Strategy Credit ( https://strateche=
